        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The Mysqli adapter has a bug that {{fetchAll()}} does not free the statement, and thus a subsequent statement fails silently, if we try to use the same Statement object.\n\n{code}\n$db = Zend_Db::factory('mysqli', ...);\n$stmt1 = $db->query('SELECT ...');\n$result1 = $stmt1->fetchAll();\n\n$stmt1 = $db->query('SELECT ...');\n$result2 = $stmt1->fetchAll();\n{code}\n\nThe second result is always empty, because the Mysqli connection cannot execute a new query until the old one is closed properly."
        },
